<br>
To everyone taking the opportunity to make sarcastic and irrelevant comments. Do you really have to piss on this one?<br>
<br>
This is a dead horse that for once may get a true and proper burial. Please have the decency to allow those that ernestly want to resolve it to work.<br>
<br>
Now, about sigs.<br>
I'm not expressing my opinions because I expect them to be agreed with totally. But collectively our thoughts may be blended into an agreeable whole.<br>
<br>
I think that the original concept of sigs were a way of visually making a statement about our characters and ourselves. Whether it's witty or morbid, ugly or cute, cuddly or repulsive, essential We're trying to elicit a response to our character (and indirectly ourselves)from those that see our sig.<br>
<br>
The only sigs I find offensive are sigs i feel were designed to be offensive. I am far more sensitive about a persons motivation behind saying or doing something than I am about what they actually do or say.<br>
<br>
This is why I think your idea for a sig test bed can be an excellent tool. To drop a sig, receive feedback, and perhaps respond to peoples concerns regarding it would allow you to get constructive critisism and  adjust a sig if you discover it's not giving the statement you intended. Then ask for mod decision if necessary.<br>
<br>
The test bed can be a kind of 'time out let's talk about that sig' place. A person who flips about a sig or a mod who thinks a sig is borderline can make a request to a poster&quot;please post in the test bed, let's talk about the sig&quot;.<br>
<br>
Side benefit: No-one derails a good thread with 'Oh man Stryven! that's a nasty sig!&quot;<br>
<br>
I would like to think that the community as a whole can respect each other enough through the process so that it isn't just more backbiting on a different thread.<br>
<br>
If I accidently yank your chain, I'm sorry, I'm just human.<br>
If I purposely yank your chain, I'm just an asshole.<br>
<br>
I'm surprised at the lack of other offended critics taking this opportunity to be productive. I know there was more of us than just me.<br>
<br>
-Stryven<br>
